        "id": 1134874
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-10-11T01:35:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think it\u0027s the \"instead\" that I find confusing, since my understanding is that Insert /will also/ not change the underlying data, since the PK is (InvocationID, IncludedInvocationID), so we wouldn\u0027t insert a new row with a different `Ready` value anyway, hence Insert will also provide idempotency.\n\nIf that matches your understanding, how about:\n\nWe use InsertOrUpdate instead of Insert to avoid errors in case the inclusion is already there. Note we also achieve idempotency as desired; CreateInclusion with the same Inclusion will just update the row with the same PK with the exact data as before, instead of creating a new entry.",
